&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;MALVERN NEIGHBOURHOOD TEAM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;ROWAN HOUSE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;NURSING ASSOCIATE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;BAND 4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;30 HOURS PER WEEK&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you an enthusiastic and motivated individual? Are you looking for a new and exciting challenge? If you answered yes to these questions then we may have the position for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking to recruit a band 4 Nursing Associate to work 30 hours per week, within our busy Neighbourhood Team, where you will be based in a beautiful location at the foot of the Malvern Hills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In this role you will be supported by a highly skilled multidisciplinary team, whilst providing support to a dedicated support team. You will be responsible for the delivery of care to the patients on the caseload,  across a broad spectrum of clinical conditions, whilst also considering the holistic needs of the patients. You will work collaboratively with the integrated team members and you will have excellent communication skills as you will also work closely with other professionals, outside agencies and family. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder is required to hold a full driving licence and have use of a vehicle in order to work in a variety of settings. You may be asked at times to cover other areas within the community care service delivery unit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information, please contact Debbie Abbots on 07753209501 or Dee Baker on 07802872579 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;All staff whatever their role, level or responsibility will be encouraged and supported to do their job well and to improve their job.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Making Every Day Better for patients, staff, service users and carers is the responsibility of all of us and we want to embed a culture within the organisation that encourages and supports the drive to improve what we do.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
